<br>
Long story...but I'm pissed and need to get it out...<br>
<br>
I entered PoV for the first time the other day and joined the other 6 people LFG....<br>
<br>
Sat there LFG for about 5 minutes.....then started inviting people....(I'm a 62 mage btw)...I invited another 62 mage, a 61 bard, a 62 paladin, a 61 ranger, and a 61 enchanter.<br>
<br>
I told them we'd be doing a melee-less group until we had a heavy healer. The paladin claimed &quot;we _had_ to have a cleric...Mobs hit for 800s here...we have to have a real healer...&quot; I asked if anyone knew a good pulling spot with a large kiting area with no pops....and non-summoning mobs that we could pull.<br>
<br>
Someone chimed in with East Wall....so we're off to the east wall. We arrive....it's not taken.....so I asked the bard to pull us a single crystal golem and kite him in front of the steps. He said no....we needed to wait for a healer. The paladin kept up his patter of &quot;we need a cleric....we need a healer....mobs hit too hard here....we'll die....&quot; ad nauseaum<br>
<br>
I saw a crystal golem...and said in group &quot;Malosini in on &lt;&lt; a Crystal Golem &gt;&gt;&quot; and ran past the group into the open kiting area siccing my pet. The other mage sicced his pet....the enchanter caught on pretty quick and said in group &quot;Slowing a Crystal Golem&quot; The ranger began arrowing the mob.<br>
<br>
You could tell the slow took....as the Golem made a beeline for the enchanter who lifted his skirts and began doing large circles while the pets gave chase. The other mage and I burned. The bard stood on the steps watching (thankfully he was at least playing the speed song). I'm arguing with the paladin in tells the whole time....He's telling me how we can't do this...I'm telling him he better be casting his stuns.....He claims he only has one stun that affects mobs this high...but that he is casting it...<br>
<br>
The Golem gets around 50% health and turns on the pets. The enchanter notices he's lost his trailer and again says &quot;Slowing a Crystal Golem&quot;. The Golem follows the enchanter untill he crashes into glassy dust at our feet. A 62nd mob brought down without any of our party taking even 1 hp of damage.<br>
<br>
I again asked the bard to pull. He says No Way. (I'm still arguing with the paladin in tells...you know the routine)... I again said in group &quot;Malosini in on &lt;&lt; a Crystal Golem &gt;&gt;&quot; and ran past the group into the open kiting area siccing my pet.<br>
<br>
Rinse - Lather - Repeat.<br>
<br>
Fluke? No we did it twice....and could probably have repeated it all day if necessary...<br>
<br>
After a second helping of this, the bard left (good he was sucking down our experience for little benefit) to be replaced by a cleric...and we went back to the old paradigm....<br>
<br>
I must say in the Paladin's defense....he was a good paladin....he took and held aggro very well.....but he couldn't seem to get his head around the idea of &quot;Not freaking getting hit!&quot;  The bard has no excuse in my opinion, you see, I played a bard to 50....sorry, played = soloed....and the bard's <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>only really reliable</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> trick is to be fast and not _get hit_....charms fail at the worst possible moment, fear-dots-snare are all resistable...but my speed keeps me alive.<br>
<br>
What is with people these days? Are they willfully ignorant? Are <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>The old ways</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the only way to accomplish anything? I love running Melee-less groups ...less risk...and when you're getting hit...there's no _doubt_ about what you are supposed to do.....GTF out of the way!<br>
<br>
&lt;/rant off&gt;<br>
<br>
