<br>
My cleric was in his mid 40's and I was playing in the Dreadlands. The zone was loaded with clerics and I could not find a grp. I was talking to a mage having the same problem and we decided to start a grp of our own. By the time we had a full grp, it consisted of a cleric, 2 mages, 2 wizzies, and an enchanter. I was the puller. Once again, I WAS THE PULLER! A cleric.... and we rocked. We were kicking a$$ and taking names. Never once did any of us come close to taking critical dmg. The mage pets were tanking. The mages and wizzies were casting dmg spells. The enchanter was mezzing, and I was healing anyone that needed healing, including the pets, after I pulled the mob back to camp. It was so great, that i started trying to get grps heavy with mages. <br>
<br>
I have also played in a 2-mage grp (with my mage) in Paludal Caverns killing fungal fiends. That grp rocked as well.<br>
<br>
I guess my point is... dont sweat the small stuff. Forget the morons. Hunt for those people that know what the real deal is.<br>
<br>
I dont remember where I read it... could have been a message thread on this board, or maybe another.... but I heard that on one of the servers there is a guild comprised of mostly mages, like maybe 90% mages, and one of their goals is to show how well mages can accomplish things.... even when the grp is mostly mages.<br>
<br>
Well, anyway, I like my cleric, but I LOVE my mage. I cant wait until he gets up into the higher lvls.<br>
<br>
